Youth feel overly criticised and ‘hang out to dry’ as critique after critique.Parents call it disrespect; youth term it a “phase of life” and boredom. Statements as hawa watoto wametushinda indicate a sharp wedge drawing blood from the lifeline of our youth, by parents and guardians.
Youth feel overly criticised and ‘hang out to dry’ as critique after critique is made over a recent scenario where young people were smoked out of a sex den. Parents call it disrespect; youth term it a “phase of life” and boredom. Glaring disconnect is an understatement as both sides await exoneration.



