Ironically, courts are full of young and old alike, caught in misdemeanours. The adage “old is gold” won’t rid the white elephant in the room. Adolescents and teens often say: “No one listens to us!” to perhaps affirm the African belief: “Children are to be seen, not heard”.
Are grown-ups guilty as charged of misconstruction to resolving the youth dilemma and perhaps considered fellow-felons? A shrill emerges, “Open not Pandora’s box; can of worms and let sleeping dogs lie”, preferring to lend a deaf ear to the youth dilemma.



