In their defence, the accused render themselves innocent until proven guilty. 
Article 6 of Unicef’s Convention on the Rights of the Child states that a child has a right to develop to “maximum extent possible”, and “States Parties recognise the right of every child to a standard of living adequate for the child’s physical, mental, spiritual, moral and social development” (Article 27).
Thus, ignorance feigned over ratified policies is no excuse in levitation of offspring birthed into harsh realties. Youth will only be plunged into further confusion, if no roundtables, anchored on goodwill, unravel mysterious sagas such as orgies, which desensitise youth consciousness.



